# Frontend Design Rules (Current)

## Primary rule
Preserve existing product visual language unless a redesign is explicitly requested.

## Component standards
- React + TypeScript + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- Keep accessibility and responsive behavior intact
- Avoid introducing visual inconsistency across dashboard pages

## UX quality checks
- No layout shift or skeleton collapse after data load
- No runtime crashes due to conditional hooks or unsafe assumptions
- Empty/error/loading states must be explicit and stable

## Performance constraints
- Avoid unnecessary rerenders
- Do not bloat bundle with new heavy deps without approval

## Delivery
For UI changes, always verify:
1) `npm run build`
2) page opens without ErrorBoundary
3) target screen renders with real API data (not static mocks)
